      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 221: Filtering deferred nodes after getKnownNodesRandom() can under-fill buckets even when other eligible known nodes exist, because skipped nodes are not replaced by additional candidates. If a bucket contains several backoff/on-demand nodes, proactive mesh maintenance may stop trying enough healthy peers. Consider fetching more candidates and selecting until the target count is reached, or adding a RoutingTable/Bucket helper that returns eligible nodes after applying shouldDeferReconnect().",
      "revId": "bb0b92a537f2552432ed7b8e14b17f16f6ace8c8",
