      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 396: The failure counter is allowed to grow to RECONNECT_ONDEMAND_THRESHOLD + 1 because the increment condition uses \u003c\u003d. The comment says it saturates at the threshold, but on the 7th failure failures becomes 7, which is inconsistent state and makes the on-demand transition depend on an off-by-one value. Saturate at the threshold and derive onDemand from \u003e\u003d threshold, e.g. ```suggestion\nif (info.failures \u003c RECONNECT_ONDEMAND_THRESHOLD)\n    info.failures++;\n...\nif (info.failures \u003e\u003d RECONNECT_ONDEMAND_THRESHOLD) {\n    info.onDemand \u003d true;\n    delay \u003d RECONNECT_MAX_DELAY;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "bb0b92a537f2552432ed7b8e14b17f16f6ace8c8",
